    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_16_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_16",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2002 BMW M3 (E46) in a condition that challenges the showroom floor. This example features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, characterized by its high-compression ratio and six individual throttle bodies, delivering a razor-sharp throttle response. The Getrag 420G six-speed manual transmission provides tactile, notch-perfect gear engagement, paired with a factory-spec variable M differential lock for optimal torque distribution. The chassis is impeccably preserved, with a verified rear subframe reinforcement and a fully serviced dual-VANOS system ensuring peak variable valve timing performance. All suspension components, including the aluminum control arms and multi-link rear assembly, maintain factory bushings with zero deflection. The exterior retains its original deep luster with no evidence of panel oxidation, while the Nappa leather interior remains supple with no bolster wear. A definitive example for the discerning purist seeking peak atmospheric performance.",
